Well I haven't posted here in like forever, but I will give this a try.../shield is used as (IMO) another taunt like feature. When I group I make hotkeys with my cleric and maybe two other &quot;thin skins.&quot; For instance I have a generic /shield hot key, target your intended grp member you wish to shield and hit the key....you will mitigate some of the damage they are taking and take a bit more your self and may also end up with the aggro again as now your dealing more damage than the thin skin is on the mob. &quot;Cleric gonna dirt napp!&quot; Donlynn hits her shield hot key &quot;&lt;SoandSo&gt; uses Donlynn as a living shield!&quot;<br>
Just con who asz you want to save and hit the shield hot key.<br>
I set up 1 or 2 hot keys for the most vulnerable in my group...mostly the cleric and the enchanter, either of those two die and your chances of survival plummet (not sure death but chances get very bad) any ways make a hot key:<br>
/shield &lt;SoandSo&gt; /shield flagelation....../shield &lt;playername&gt;<br>
Get it? This is a great tool to have on groups that exploring, sucks on raids cuz ya never know which way to point you &quot;save thier asz key&quot; and besides to many things to do on a raid only complicate things.<br>
